<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,793,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,793,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(1) Body robust; (2) anterior margin of head broadly rounded; (3) frons, in anterior view, with slight concavity on superior portion; (4) antennal ledge, in frontal view, protuberant, oblique, and carinate externally; (5) frontogenal suture extending onto crown and attaining ocellus; (6) pronotum with pair of broad shallow depressions on anterior half; (7) forewing with appendix narrow and short, restricted to outer border of first apical cell and part of second apical cell, (8) apical cells short, and (9) extra crossveins may be present in anteapical cells, costal apical cell, and clavus; (10) hind wing with vein R2+3 incomplete; (11) first valvifer of female (unknown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,265,1010,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aguana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="russata">
<emphasis box="[151,265,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">A. russata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with basiventral spiniform process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,793,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1045,1070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">Remarks.</emphasis>
The following features mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Young, D. A." box="[754,910,1046,1070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 1135" refId="ref5610" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, i-vi + 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young (1977)</bibRefCitation>
cannot be regarded as diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1926" box="[1341,1428,1046,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aguana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1341,1428,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">Aguana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (1) style without a preapical lobe, which does not apply to the two new species described here; (2) aedeagus with a pair of apical processes (
<taxonomicName authority="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli, 2019" authorityName="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2019" box="[431,589,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aguana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picinguaba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[431,589,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">A. picinguaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,686,1117,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,686,1117,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has no processes and they are very small in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli, 2019" authorityName="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2019" box="[1190,1281,1118,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aguana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spitzi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1190,1281,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">A. spitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1288,1378,1117,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1288,1378,1117,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
); (3) hind wing with vein R2+3 complete (in all specimens examined here this vein is incomplete).
</paragraph>
